subsection.def:
cargo
                    (貨物) means any goods, wares, merchandise and
                articles of any kind carried in a container;

inspector
                    (督察) means an inspector appointed under
                    section 18;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an owner, that it was an express term of the bailment or
                    lease that the bailee or lessee, as the case may be, should be responsible for
                    ensuring compliance with that requirement;

in the case of a lessee, that he had become a lessor under a further lease
                    and that it was an express term of the further lease that the further lessee
                    should be responsible for ensuring compliance with that requirement;

provide that the contravention of any particular regulation is an offence,
                    and may prescribe penalties for any such offence of a fine at level 4 or 1
                    year’s imprisonment or both such fine and such imprisonment;

provide for the issue and service of notice of any inspection or of any
                    findings in respect of a matter specified in section 14,
                        15 or 16;
